Record Class Scenario

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
dev.royalcore.api.scenario.Scenario
Record Components:
name - the display name of the scenario
itemConsumer - item configuration and custom items used by this scenario
listenerConsumer - event listeners associated with this scenario
commandConsumer - commands exposed by this scenario
borderConsumer - world border configuration for this scenario
settingsConsumer - configurable settings for this scenario
schedulerConsumer - scheduled tasks associated with this scenario
messageConsumer - messages used by this scenario
priority - priority of this scenario when resolving order
scenarioConflicts - scenarios that cannot be enabled together with this one
requiredScenarios - scenarios that must also be enabled for this one to be valid
playerConsumer - per-player behaviour applied when the scenario starts
onStart - callback invoked when the scenario starts
onStop - callback invoked when the scenario stops
resourcepackConsumer - resource packs that must be applied
public record Scenario(net.kyori.adventure.text.Component name, ItemConsumer itemConsumer, ListenerConsumer listenerConsumer, CommandConsumer commandConsumer, BorderConsumer borderConsumer, SettingsConsumer settingsConsumer, SchedulerConsumer schedulerConsumer, MessageConsumer messageConsumer, ScenarioPriority priority, List<Scenario> scenarioConflicts, List<Scenario> requiredScenarios, PlayerConsumer playerConsumer, Runnable onStart, Runnable onStop, ResourcePackConsumer resourcepackConsumer) extends Record
Represents a single scenario definition for a Battle Royale game.

A scenario aggregates item, listener, command, border, settings, scheduler, message and player behaviour, along with dependencies and lifecycle callbacks.
